vulnerability.name: USN-6183-2
vulnerability.description: USN-6183-1 fixed vulnerabilities in Bind. This update provides the corresponding updates for Ubuntu 14.04 LTS, Ubuntu 16.04 LTS and Ubuntu 18.04 LTS.  Original advisory details:   Shoham Danino, Anat Bremler-Barr, Yehuda Afek, and Yuval Shavitt discovered  that Bind incorrectly handled the cache size limit. A remote attacker could  possibly use this issue to consume memory, leading to a denial of service.  (CVE-2023-2828)    It was discovered that Bind incorrectly handled the recursive-clients  quota. A remote attacker could possibly use this issue to cause Bind to  crash, resulting in a denial of service. This issue only affected Ubuntu  22.04 LTS, Ubuntu 22.10, and Ubuntu 23.04. (CVE-2023-2911)

statements.status_notes: Bind could be made to crash if it received specially crafted network traffic. Available with Ubuntu Pro.
